@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Working Class**: The urban working class - blue-collar workers in factories, workshops, mines, and the like. Most are socialist, supporting either the RSDRP or other left-wing parties. They make up 30-35% of the population.

**Bourgeoisie**: The Bourgeoisie consists of independent artisans, shopkeepers, and small-time businesspeople. They tend to be conservative and are the strongest base for the nationalist parties. 10-15% of the population.

**Intelligensia**: The educated middle class consists of white-collar workers and government employees. This is the base of liberalism. 10% of the population.

**Peasantry**: Small and large farmers and independent rural workers. The Peasants often support the PSR or, to a lesser extent, the VS. ~40% of the population.

**Muslims** are the largest minority, at about 11% or 12% of the population. They disproportionately support the Müsavat Party.

**Jews** account for between 4% to 5% of the population, and tend to support Socialist parties, mostly the RSDRP(O), although substantial numbers support the Jewish National Bloc.


