@parties
go-to: menu

**RSDRP(O)** - *Rossijskaja Social-Demokratičeskaja Rabočaja Partija (Ob’jedinjonnaja)* (Russian Social Democratic Labour Party (United)) - this is us. We are a socialist and democratic party of the working class. We are the heirs of the legacy of Marx and Engels, Martov and Plekhanov. We are the foremost defenders of the Republic. The modern RSDRP(O) is the continuation of the Menshevik sections of the RSDRP.

**PSR** - *Pártiya Sotsialístov-Revolyutsionérov* (Party of Socialists-Revolutionaries) - a left-populist, Narodist party that supports the Republic, and has historically supported many of our labor, welfare, and anti-militarist priorities. They have often been in coalitions with us. [? if year >= 1930 or chancellor = "Brüning" : They have appeared to take a more conservative turn recently, with the rise of Brüning and the party leader, Ludwig Kaas. ?]

Current relations: [+ z_relation : relationships +]

# TODO: replace this with the german state party after 1930
**K-D** - *Konstitutsionno-Demokraticheskaya Partiya/Pártiya Naródnoy Svobódy* (Constitutional Democratic Party, or officially the Party of People's Freedom ) - a centrist to center-right liberal party, popular among the intelligensia and educated middle class. They have historically been cordial with us but, especially following their recent conservative turn, oppose our economic policies. The **Alash Party** is closely tied to the Kadets, generally considered to be their counterpart in Russian Central Asia. [? if year >= 1930 : They have recently reformed themselves as the German State Party (DStP). ?]

Current relations: [+ ddp_relation : relationships +]

**VS** - *Vserossiyskiy Soyuz* (All-Russian Union) - a conservative party, supported by the middle classes and rural conservatives. They despise us.

Current relations: [+ dnvp_relation : relationships +]

**Müsavat** - *Müsavat Firqəsi* (Müsavat Party) - a pan-Muslim liberal party, with pan-Turkist, conservative, and even Socialist elements. It is supported by a broad coalition of Muslims, from left to right. We have entered coalition talks with them before, though they led to nowhere.

Current relations: [+ dvp_relation : relationships +]

**PLSRI** - *Partiya Levykh Sotsialistov-Revolyutsionerov-Internatsionalistov* (Party of Left Socialist-Revolutionaries-Internationalists) - a radical left-wing offshoot of the PSR that emerged in the aftermath of the failed Bolshevik Revolution of 1917, they are split between former Bolsheviks and Narodists. The party is currently crippled by internal fighting, which is unlikely to end soon. 

Current relations: [+ kpd_relation : relationships +]

[? if sapd_formed: **RSDRPI** - *Rossijskaja Social-Demokratičeskaja Rabočaja Partija internatsionalistov* (Russian Social Democratic Labour Party of Internationalists) - a party recently formed in a split from the RSDRP(O), the RSDRPI is essentially an agglomeration of various left-wing splinter groups between the RSRDP(O) and PLSRI. ?]

**SRN** - *Soyuz Russkogo Naroda* - (Union of the Russian People, or Black-Hundredists) - a far-right ultranationalist, monarchist, and reactionary party. Led by Vladimir Purishkevich, many of their members and leaders supported Wrangel's attempted rebellion, and were nearly banned for it.

Current relations: [+ nsdap_relation : relationships +]

**Other parties** - there is a multitude of small, mostly conservative, regionalist, or socialist parties, such as the Labourist Popular-Socialist Party, the Armenian Populist Party, the All-Peasant Union, and others. Their political position usually lies between the RSDRP and VS.

@paramilitaries
on-arrival: {!
Q.rb_strength = Math.round(Q.rb_strength);
Q.sh_strength = Math.round(Q.sh_strength);
Q.sa_strength = Math.round(Q.sa_strength); 
!}
go-to: menu

**Paramilitary groups:**

**Soyuz Fevralya** (SF): The *Union of February* is an organization affiliated with many of the left-democratic parties - the RSDRP, PSR, and other minor groups, but primarily with the RSDRP. Historically, this has been an unarmed organization.

Strength: [+ rb_strength +] thousand

Militarization: [+ rb_militancy : militancy +]

**Krasnaya Gvardiya (KG)**: The "*Red Guard*" is associated with the PLSRI and, unofficially, the banned Bolsheviks.

Strength: [+ rfb_strength +] thousand

Militarization: [+ rfb_militancy : militancy +]

**Russkiy Obshche-Voinskiy Soyuz (ROVS)**: A right-wing nationalist organization of primarily Great War veterans, the *Russian All-Military Union* has no official stance on the Republic, hosting both pro- and anti-republican voices. Associated with the conservative and right-democratic parties, including the Kadets and VS.

Strength: [+ sh_strength +] thousand

Militarization: [+ sh_militancy : militancy +]

**Znamya (Z)**: The *Banner* is the amalgamation of previous Black-Hundredist paramilitaries into one, they are associated with the SRN.

Strength: [+ sa_strength +] thousand

Militarization: [+ sa_militancy : militancy +]

**Official military/paramilitary groups:**

**Russkaya Armiya**: [+ reichswehr_strength +] thousand troops. This is Russia's military.

Loyalty: [+ reichswehr_loyalty : loyalty +]

**Petrogradskaya Gvardiya**: [+ prussian_police_strength +] thousand members.

Loyalty: [+ prussian_police_loyalty : loyalty +]



@factions
go-to: neorevisionists if neorevisionism > 0; menu if neorevisionism <= 0

**Internal factions of the SPD**

Overall dissent: [+ dissent_percent : dissent +]

**Internationalists**

The Internationalists are the left-wing of the  RSDRP(O), staunch Marxists who believe that class struggle, historical materialism, and revolution are the principles that should guide the Party. Historically, they pushed for an immediate end to the Great War without territorial changes, putting them at odds with the Economists.
Strength: [+ left_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ left_dissent : dissent +]

**Centrists**

The Centrists in the RSDRP(O) are followers of the doctrine of orthodox Marxism as expounded by Karl Kautsky and Julius Martov. They seek a middle course between reform and revolution, while defending the democratic republic.

Strength: [+ center_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ center_dissent : dissent +]

**Labor**

Many RSDRP(O) members are also part of the Vseobshchya Konfederatsya Profsoyuzov (VKP), or General Confederation of Trade Unions. Their goal is economic reform and benefits for organized workers.

Strength: [+ labor_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ labor_dissent : dissent +]

**Economists**

The Economists are pragmatic participants in government, and seek to expand the welfare state and defend democracy against the conservatism, ultranationalism, and revolution. The Economists are the party-right, composed of Great War Defencists and young Socialists alike. [? if spd_prussia : They are dominant in the state governments of West Russia. ?]

Strength: [+ reformist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ reformist_dissent : dissent +]

@neorevisionists
go-to: menu

**Neodefencists**

Neodefencists focus on defending the republic and expanding democracy, while also expanding the party's base beyond the working class to create a people's party. They support new propaganda methods and extraparliamentary action in defense of the republic.

Strength: [+ neorevisionist_strength : strength +]

Dissent: [+ neorevisionist_dissent : dissent +]


@figures
title: Figures and Charts
go-to: menu
on-arrival: z_minus_bvp_r = z_r - 3;
on-display: {!
data = [
    {
        "id": "kpd",
        "legend": "KPD",
        "name": "KPD",
        "seats": Q.kpd_r*5,
    }];
if (Q.sapd_formed && Q.sapd_r) {
    data.push({
            "id": "sapd",
            "legend": "SAPD",
            "name": "SAPD",
            "seats": Math.round(Q.sapd_r*5),
            });
}
data = data.concat([
    {
        "id": "spd",
        "legend": "SPD",
        "name": "SPD",
        "seats": Q.spd_r*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "ddp",
        "legend": "DDP",
        "name": "DDP",
        "seats": Q.ddp_r*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "z",
        "legend": "Center",
        "name": "Center",
        "seats": (Q.z_r - 3)*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "bvp",
        "legend": "BVP",
        "name": "BVP",
        "seats": 3*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "dvp",
        "legend": "DVP",
        "name": "DVP",
        "seats": Q.dvp_r*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "other",
        "legend": "Other",
        "name": "Other",
        "seats": Q.other_r*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "dnvp",
        "legend": "DNVP",
        "name": "DNVP",
        "seats": Q.dnvp_r*5,
    },
    {
        "id": "nsdap",
        "legend": "NSDAP",
        "name": "NSDAP",
        "seats": Q.nsdap_r*5,
    },
]);
if (d3 && window) {
    // get screen width
    var width = 500;
    var height = 500;
    var screenWidth = document.getElementById('content').offsetWidth;
    if (screenWidth < width - 50) {
        width = screenWidth - 50;
        height = width;
        document.getElementById("reichstag").style.height = screenWidth/2 + "px";
    }
    var parliament = d3.parliament();
    parliament.width(width).height(height).innerRadiusCoef(0.4);
    parliament.enter.fromCenter(true).smallToBig(true);
    parliament.exit.toCenter(false).bigToSmall(true);
    d3.select("#reichstag").datum(data).call(parliament);

    var lines = d3.linegraph(false, false,
            Q.parties,
            {'spd': '#E3000F', 'kpd': '#8B0000', 'ddp': '#DCCA4A', 'z': '#000', 'dvp': '#D5AC27', 'dnvp': '#3f7bc1', 'nsdap': '#954B00', 'other': '#a0a0a0', 'sapd': '#c40000'},
            {'spd': 'SPD', 'kpd': 'KPD', 'ddp': Q.ddp_name, 'z': 'Z + BVP', 'dvp': 'DVP', 'dnvp': 'DNVP', 'nsdap': 'NSDAP', 'other': 'Others', 'sapd': 'SAPD'});
    lines.width(width).height(400);
    //var svg = lines(Q.election_records);
    if (Q.election_records.length > 0) {
        d3.select("#election_history").datum(Q.election_records).call(lines);
    }
    //document.getElementById('election_history').innerHTML = svg.outerHTML;

    // party support records should not have so many ticks
    if (!Q.historical_mode || Q.game_over) {
        var lines_2 = d3.linegraph(true, true,
            Q.parties,
            {'spd': '#E3000F', 'kpd': '#8B0000', 'ddp': '#DCCA4A', 'z': '#000', 'dvp': '#D5AC27', 'dnvp': '#3f7bc1', 'nsdap': '#954B00', 'other': '#a0a0a0', 'sapd': '#c40000'},
            {'spd': 'SPD', 'kpd': 'KPD', 'ddp': Q.ddp_name, 'z': 'Z + BVP', 'dvp': 'DVP', 'dnvp': 'DNVP', 'nsdap': 'NSDAP', 'other': 'Others', 'sapd': 'SAPD'});
        lines_2.width(width).height(400);
        d3.select("#party_support_history").datum(Q.party_support_records).call(lines_2);
    }

    // economic stats
    var minInflation = d3.min(Q.economic_records, d => d.inflation);
    var maxUnemployment = d3.max(Q.economic_records, d => d.unemployment);
    var lines_3 = d3.linegraph(true, true, ['inflation', 'unemployment'],
            {'inflation': '#0000FF', 'unemployment': '#FF0000'},
            {'inflation': 'Inflation', 'unemployment': 'Unemployment'},
            maxUnemployment + 5, minInflation - 5, 21);
    lines_3.width(width).height(300);
    d3.select("#economic_history").datum(Q.economic_records).call(lines_3);
}
!}

